.cs 7 on
.item 'SET MESSAGE Command' 'Added 07/08/82 by LSO'
.boxon
SET MESSAGE [message]
.boxoff

.* DESCRIPTION
Required Privileges:  OPERATOR or SYSTEMS

The SET MESSAGE command sets the system message in the current subsystem of
WYLBUR that would be displayed to users when they logon or with a BROADCAST
command.

.* SELECT 'SET MESSAGE Command Options'
.us Option Descriptions

.* OPTION MESSAGE
.ix message 'on SET MESSAGE Command'
message\\\\\\\\\a one line message that cannot exceed 255 characters.  If
                there is no message, the system message will be removed.
.cs 7 off
